FBIS4-39300 "drsov109_a_94025" FBIS-SOV-94-109 Daily Report 7 Jun 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS UN Peacekeeper Seriously Wounded in Sarajevo UN Peacekeeper Seriously Wounded in Sarajevo LD0706015094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0055 GMT 7 Jun 94 LD0706015094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Russian BFN [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Boris Sitnikov] [Text] UN, 7 Jun--A Russian serviceman who is a member of the UN Protection Forces has been seriously wounded in Sarajevo. This was reported here on Monday by Fred Ekhard, official representative of the UN secretary general. "The Russian soldier was seriously wounded by sniper fire in Sarajevo on Sunday. Thus, the total number of casualties among the staff of the UN Protection Forces is 1,014 wounded and 90 killed. Only a small part of these casualties have been caused by the Bosnian Serbs," Ekhard noted.
